From 3f8ab8c4f2660eaab3e3a03b1cd219cbe0b10dac Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Enrique Parodi Spalazzi <enrique.parodi@airbus.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 00:17:38 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 01/10] feat[core,lang]: tolerant scanner, recoverable parser,
 structured diagnostics

Substrate for later editor-services APIs (tokenize, validate, complete,
guideAt). The parser/scanner can now produce position-bearing diagnostics
rather than throwing, so tools can render partial information on
in-flight input.

- TextSpan and a structured Diagnostic type with severity, code, and
  position. Diagnostic codes are a closed enum so consumers can dispatch
  on them.
- Tolerant scanner mode: emit diagnostics for unexpected bytes and
  unclosed strings instead of throwing, and keep scanning past the
  error.
- Recoverable parser entry point (parseQueryTolerant,
  parseFileTolerant): synchronize on statement boundaries and record
  parse errors as diagnostics.
- AST span coverage: every statement and expression carries the source
  range it covered, prerequisite for span-based highlighting and
  cursor-local tooling.
- Grammar tightening: FROM requires <session>.<bus> (no wildcards in the
  FROM clause); equality and non-range comparisons no longer chain
  (a < b < c and a = b = c are rejected; combine with AND).

Expanded Stage 1 test coverage and restored FailedCheckHandler wiring
across the affected fixtures.
